[1]
Date: Wed 9 Oct 2002
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Agencia EFE (via COMTEX), Wed 9 Oct 2002 [edited]

Puerto Rico: 18 Confirmed Cases of Dengue Hemorrhagic Fever
--------------------------------------------------
A total of 18 cases of hemorrhagic dengue fever have been confirmed in
Puerto Rico during the first 9 months of this year, health officials said.
Patricia Cano, a Health Ministry expert on dengue fever, said on Tue 8 Oct
2002 that so far this year, 33 percent of the 2003 people believed infected
with dengue fever have tested positive for the disease. "A total of 18
cases of dengue hemorrhagic fever has been reported by 28 Sep 2002," Cano
said. Some 289 suspected cases of dengue fever were reported in September
of 2002, compared with 708 cases during the same month in 2001.
To date, a 15-year-old girl has been the only fatality from dengue
hemorrhagic fever in Puerto Rico. "The number of cases so far has been
within forecast, perhaps a little lower than last year," Cano said. Dengue
fever cases have been falling off in Puerto Rico as a result of a campaign
launched in May to fumigate high-risk communities.
